Available Storage Devices: * lsblk

Observation: Displays a tree-like view of all block devices (hard drives, partitions) attached to the system.

Mounted File Systems and Disk Usage: * df -h

Observation: Shows the total, used, and available space on all mounted file systems in a human-readable format (Gigabytes/Megabytes).

Inode Utilization: * df -i

Observation: Displays how many inodes (file index entries) are used and available. Running out of inodes prevents new file creation even if there is physical disk space left.

Using vi to Document:

Type vi Storage_Assessment_Report.txt

Press i to enter Insert Mode and type your findings based on the df and lsblk outputs.

Press Esc to exit Insert Mode, then type :wq and press Enter to write (save) the file and quit the editor.
